# orca-wasm/orca is a shallow clone of the OrcaSlicer submodule fetched by CI
# (build-wasm.yml) or manually per MT-PLAN.md Phase 0 — .gitmodules already
# declares `ignore = all` for it, but that only applies when it's checked out
# via `git submodule update`; a plain `git clone` into the same path (as
# MT-PLAN.md's inventory step does) isn't covered by that, hence this entry.
orca-wasm/orca/
# orca-wasm/deps-install(-st|-mt) and build-wasm(-st|-mt) are build-wasm.yml's
# (and its local reproduction's — see MT-PLAN.md Phase 4) own dep-install and
# CMake build output dirs. CI never needed this entry (its runners are
# ephemeral, so the directory never outlives a single job), but a local build
# inside a real checkout leaves it sitting in the working tree.
orca-wasm/deps-install*/
orca-wasm/build-wasm*/
